==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Preconceive
<hw>Pre`con*ceive"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Preconceived</conjf>
<pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Preconceiving</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To conceive, or form an
opinion of, beforehand; to form a previous notion or idea of.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In a dead plain the way seemeth the longer, because the eye hath
<qex>preconceived</qex> it shorter than the truth.</q>
<rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Preconception</ent>⟦br⟧
